{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dfb9edde-1e25-4ebd-b588-eba903d30726","content":"Here's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP):\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --collect-coverage \\\n  --collect-coverage-settings cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump \\\n  --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\nEverything after `--` is passed directly to the MTP runner.\n\n**Required NuGet packages** in your test project:\n\n| Package | Replaces |\n|---|---|\n| `Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild` | enables MTP via `dotnet test` |\n| `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` | `--logger trx` |\n| `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` |\n| `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` | `--blame-crash` |\n| `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` | `--blame-hang` |\n\n**Key mapping:**\n\n| VSTest flag | MTP flag |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--collect-coverage --collect-coverage-settings cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n| `--filter` | `--filter` (still works through `dotnet test`) |\n\nAlso set `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` in your test project's `<PropertyGroup>` (or `Directory.Build.props`) to opt into MTP mode.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"950bebfe-123f-46a9-96cf-8e54e85cd6ce","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating a `dotnet test` command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing tooling migration. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences when moving to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n1. `--filter` becomes `--filter` (same) or `--test-filter` depending on the runner\n2. `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n3. `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--collect-coverage` with Microsoft.CodeCoverage, or you use a different mechanism\n\n\n4. Blame-related flags like `--blame-crash`, `--blame-hang`, and `--blame-hang-timeout` map to `--crashdump`, `--hangdump`, and `--hangdump-timeout` respectively.\n\nWith MTP, the test executable itself acts as the runner, though `dotnet test` can still orchestrate it. The filter syntax changes slightlyâ€”`--treenode-filter` is the new approach, though legacy `--filter` syntax may still be supported for backward compatibility.\n\nOther flag mappings include `--logger trx` becoming `--report-trx`, `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` becoming `--collect-coverage`, and each of these features requires its corresponding NuGet package like `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` or `Microsoft.CodeCoverage`.\n\nWhen using `dotnet test` with MTP, I need to pass MTP-specific options after the `--` separator. In .NET 9+, `dotnet test` has native MTP support, though .NET 8 might require the `Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild` package. The command would look like passing the filter before the separator and then all the MTP options after it, or if running the test executable directly, the syntax changes slightly.\n\nFor .NET 8 specifically, I need to ensure the right NuGet packages are installed: the MSBuild integration package, TRX reporting, code coverage extensions, and crash dump support.\n\nThe command structure uses `dotnet test` with the filter passed before the `--` separator, then the MTP-specific options follow. For code coverage in cobertura format, I'd need to reference a configuration file that specifies the output format, or potentially inline the settings depending on what the Microsoft.CodeCoverage package supports.","outputTokens":1577,"requestId":"340B:37A92F:7280A5E:7ED61C1:69F3FAFF"},"id":"0f671544-19cb-4df3-9bde-30658d53c626","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:00:11.273Z","parentId":"9c3361f0-955d-4e5e-b1a0-a071e4c8bcf6"}
